summary: This is a subpoena issued by the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York to the School District of Palm Beach County, commanding it to produce student records for a specific individual and to appear in court on November 29, 2021, in relation to the case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell, which is the subject of this subpoena.

persons.name: Audrey Stra
persons.context: Issued the subpoena on behalf of the United States Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.

events.title: Scheduled Court Appearance for School District
events.description: The School District of Palm Beach County is commanded to appear in court to testify and produce records in the case against Ghislaine Maxwell.

events.title: Subpoena Issued
events.description: The subpoena was issued by the U.S. Attorney's Office to compel the School District of Palm Beach County to produce student records.

keyFacts: The subpoena seeks student records from the School District of Palm Beach County for an individual whose name and date of birth are redacted.
The records requested include registration paperwork and student files related to enrollment at a school in West Palm Beach, Florida.
The subpoena is part of the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)).
Failure to comply with the subpoena constitutes contempt of court and may result in civil sanctions and criminal penalties.
